Goal : Implement authorization using Pano2 PAD service. Components to Import from Pano2: PadClient - HTTP client for PAD API UserPermissionsCache - Caching layer Permissions` model - User permissions structure *}}Adaptation Required:{{* Map PAD entitlements to RulePermissions Examples of rulespace/scope names: ruleSpace: te-ctp 
scope: ny5-te-isi1 Custom entitlement codes for Rules service (see below, possible to do?): RULE_VIEW_{RULESPACE}→ any access (see below)

RULE_VIEW_{SCOPE}→ VIEW access 
RULE_EDIT_{SCOPE} → EDIT access 
RULE_PROMOTE_{SCOPE} → PROMOTE access

RULE_ADMIN → Global admin access Implementation (PadAuthorizationProvider.java): @Service
@ConditionalOnProperty(name = "rule.security.provider", havingValue = "pad")
public class PadAuthorizationProvider implements RuleAuthorizationProvider {

    private final UserPermissionsCache permissionsCache;

    @Override
    public boolean hasAccess(String userId, String ruleSpace,
                            String scope, AccessLevel level) {
        Permissions permissions = permissionsCache.getPermissionsByUserId(userId);
        return checkEntitlement(permissions, ruleSpace, scope, level);
    }

    private boolean checkEntitlement(Permissions perms,
                                     String ruleSpace,
                                     String scope,
                                     AccessLevel level) {
        // Check for admin entitlement
        if (perms.getEntitlements().contains("RULE_ADMIN")) {
            return true;
        }

        // Check level-specific entitlement
        // TODO: how to handle special characters in rulespace name - e.g. '-'
        String entitlement = String.format("RULE_%s_%s",
            level.name(), ruleSpace.toUpperCase());
        return perms.getEntitlements().contains(entitlement);
    }
