This feature leverages  User Custom Configs  (see  ).  It allows Redux actions to be logged on the backend for debugging user interactions.  Configuration is controlled through custom configs provided by developers. Config Fields ACTION_LOGGER_INCLUSIONS Type: string (comma-separated) Matches alphanumeric text and "*" wildcard Case-insensitive Examples: "hot button" → matches "[User action] Hot Button triggered" "*" → matches all actions (recommended default if log volume is acceptable) "abc,def" → matches "zdefz" ACTION_LOGGER_EXCLUSIONS Type: string (comma-separated) Same rules as  ACTION_LOGGER_INCLUSIONS Used to suppress noisy actions Recommended defaults: {
    "ACTION_LOGGER_EXCLUSIONS": "Set time,Set system status,Clear system status,Market data*Fetch,Point of presence*Fetch active status",
    "ACTION_LOGGER_INCLUSIONS": "*",
    "STATE_DUMP": true
} STATE_DUMP On error screen "Oops! It looks like something went wrong." a button allows Redux state download A new menu item also allows Redux state download at any time Users can send this state to floor support for troubleshooting

