Context This relates to Polaris IL-3631 - where CO subscription requests stop working. Happens 2-3 times a day and likely related to CloudFlare. This PAN is to fix a long-standing bug in Polaris where it does not close subscriptions prior to starting new ones. AMS does. The likelihood that this PAN fixes the bug is a finger-in-the-wind better than 50% See this page for the full list of ruggedization improvements  Pol Client ruggedization improvements Requirement When a PO is selected, close the websocket connection for the prior PO before opening the a new connection/subscription for the new PO . See below for details. Analysis Polaris does NOT close websocket connections for discarded subscriptions.  AMS does . This is primarily due to the different  routeParameterChangedStrategy  between AMS and WS in client/src/app/child-order/child-order.context.ts: ams = 'update' ws = 'reload' As a result, in rx-provider-utils.ts , rxProvider.updateRouteParams() - which cleans up the existing subscription, is executed for AMS but not for WS if (!isEmpty(previousRouteParameters) && !isEmpty(routeParameters) && routeParameterChangedStrategy === 'update') {
  rxProvider.updateRouteParams(routeParameters);
  return;
} To do Modify the above code snippet to cancel the old subscriptions when  routeParameterChangedStrategy === 'reload'.   Will need the following changes 1. rxprovider - new method cancelCurrentSubscriptions() - posts a new messageType "cancelCurrentSubscriptions"
2. rxprovider.terminate - add a call to cancelCurrentSubscriptions() before killing the liveWorkers.
3. worker-utils.ts - handle the new "cancelCurrentSubscriptions" msgType, call publisher.cancelCurrentSubscriptions()
4. publisher - new method cancelCurrentSubscriptions() does:  this.clients.snapshotClient?.cancel() & this.clients.updatesClient?.cancel(); See attached call-tree file to help understand where to make changes -  Polaris and AMS call chain when PO is selected.txt Notes on the fix This fix w…

